Elizabeth Warren za ta "yi zurfin tunani" kan yiwuwar tsayawa takarar shugaban kasa a 2020, in ji Sanata daga Massachusetts
Sanata Elizabeth Warren ta Massachusetts ta ce a ranar Asabar za ta "yi zurfin tunani" kan yiwuwar tsayawa takarar shugaban kasa bayan zaben da za a yi tsakanin 'yan takara.
A lokacin wani muhawara na jama'a a Holyoke, Massachusetts, Warren ya tabbatar da cewa zai yi la'akari da yiwuwar tsayawa takara.
"Lokaci ya yi da mata za su je Washington don gyara gwamnatinmu da ta lalace, kuma hakan ya haɗa da mace a matsayin babban mai alhakin", in ji ta, a cewar The Hill.
"Bayan 6 ga Nuwamba, zan yi zurfin tunani game da neman takarar shugaban kasa".
Warren ya yi tsokaci kan shugaba Donald Trump a lokacin muhawara, yana mai cewa "yana kai kasar cikin hanyar da ba ta dace ba".
"Ina matukar damuwa game da abin da Donald Trump ke yi wa dimokiradiyarmu", in ji ta.
Warren ya kasance mai sukar Trump da kuma wanda ya nada shi a matsayin mai shari'a a Kotun Koli, Brett Kavanaugh.
A cikin wata sanarwa ta Twitter a ranar Juma'a, Warren ya ce "a bayyane yake muna bukatar binciken FBI kafin a kada kuri'a".
Amma, wani zabe da aka gudanar a ranar Alhamis ya nuna cewa yawancin masu zabe na Warren ba su yarda cewa ta tsaya takarar shugaban kasa ba a shekarar 2020.
Kashi 59 cikin 100 na masu jefa kuri'a a Massachusetts sun ce bai kamata ta tsaya takara ba, a cewar wani bincike da Cibiyar Bincike ta Siyasa ta Jami'ar Suffolk/Boston Globe ta gudanar.
